{"line":"{\"type\":\"assistant\",\"message\":{\"model\":\"claude-opus-4-6\",\"id\":\"msg_01WG1sxY4LpVkLgK77sBY1MC\",\"type\":\"message\",\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Here's a concise summary of **cc-manager**:\\n\\n**Purpose:** An interactive terminal app that places a **controller agent** (Codex CLI) in front of **Claude Code**. The controller acts like a developer managing Claude Code on behalf of the user — it decides whether to answer directly or delegate work to Claude Code, then reviews results before continuing.\\n\\n**Control loop:** User → Controller (Codex) decides → optionally launches Claude Code → Controller reviews output & repo state → repeats or emits STOP → shell stays open for the next instruction.\\n\\n**Setup:**\\n- Requires Node 18.17+\\n- `npm install && npm link`\\n\\n**Usage modes:**\\n1. **Interactive shell** — run `cc-manager` in a repo directory. Supports commands like `/new`, `/resume`, `/status`, `/list`, `/logs`, `/detach`, `/quit`.\\n2. **One-shot** — `cc-manager run \\\"<message>\\\"` processes until STOP then exits. Also supports `resume`, `status`, `logs`, `list`, and `doctor` subcommands.\\n\\n**Key design:**\\n- Controller (Codex) only inspects/verifies — never edits files directly.\\n- Worker (Claude Code) performs actual repo changes using allowed tools (`Bash`, `Read`, `Edit`).\\n- Same Claude session is reused across worker turns within a run.\\n- Runs are persisted under `.cc-manager/runs/<run-id>/` with manifests, events, transcripts, and per-request logs.\\n- Tests use fake Codex/Claude binaries to verify the control loop end-to-end (`npm test`).\"}],\"stop_reason\":null,\"stop_sequence\":null,\"usage\":{\"input_tokens\":1,\"cache_creation_input_tokens\":2217,\"cache_read_input_tokens\":21182,\"cache_creation\":{\"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens\":0,\"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens\":2217},\"output_tokens\":1,\"service_tier\":\"standard\",\"inference_geo\":\"not_available\"},\"context_management\":null},\"parent_tool_use_id\":null,\"session_id\":\"076ed951-b233-4f01-9f84-929dcf77822b\",\"uuid\":\"6b6578d0-b98b-4b86-be03-f18b02544a81\"}","parsed":{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01WG1sxY4LpVkLgK77sBY1MC","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Here's a concise summary of **cc-manager**:\n\n**Purpose:** An interactive terminal app that places a **controller agent** (Codex CLI) in front of **Claude Code**. The controller acts like a developer managing Claude Code on behalf of the user — it decides whether to answer directly or delegate work to Claude Code, then reviews results before continuing.\n\n**Control loop:** User → Controller (Codex) decides → optionally launches Claude Code → Controller reviews output & repo state → repeats or emits STOP → shell stays open for the next instruction.\n\n**Setup:**\n- Requires Node 18.17+\n- `npm install && npm link`\n\n**Usage modes:**\n1. **Interactive shell** — run `cc-manager` in a repo directory. Supports commands like `/new`, `/resume`, `/status`, `/list`, `/logs`, `/detach`, `/quit`.\n2. **One-shot** — `cc-manager run \"<message>\"` processes until STOP then exits. Also supports `resume`, `status`, `logs`, `list`, and `doctor` subcommands.\n\n**Key design:**\n- Controller (Codex) only inspects/verifies — never edits files directly.\n- Worker (Claude Code) performs actual repo changes using allowed tools (`Bash`, `Read`, `Edit`).\n- Same Claude session is reused across worker turns within a run.\n- Runs are persisted under `.cc-manager/runs/<run-id>/` with manifests, events, transcripts, and per-request logs.\n- Tests use fake Codex/Claude binaries to verify the control loop end-to-end (`npm test`)."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":2217,"cache_read_input_tokens":21182,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":2217},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"076ed951-b233-4f01-9f84-929dcf77822b","uuid":"6b6578d0-b98b-4b86-be03-f18b02544a81"}}
